annotations:
CHARMM27 dynamics simulation trajectories of -conotoxin LsIA and its C-terminal carboxylated analogue bound at 3 2 nAChR
The whole simulation trajectories (28 individual trajectories with 27ns for each) contain the coordinates and parameters of atoms with time for -conotoxin LsIA and its C-terminal carboxylated analogue anchored to rat 3 2 nAChR, respectively. The GROMACS 4.6.5 with the CHARMM27 force field is used for the simulation. The trajectory (.xtc) files are saved every 100ps time for each protein complex only. The portable binary run input (.tpr) files are also uploaded with the data.
